text: The Sydney Football Club was an Australian rules football club founded in 1881 and based in Sydney.http://australianfootball.com/clubs/stats/sydney%2B%2528original%2529/244/ In 1886 the club went undefeated winning 12 games and drawing 2. In that season, they scored 52 goals, the record for goals scored up to that point. ==References== Category:Football in Australia Category:1881 establishments in Australia Category:1954 disestablishments in Australia Category:Australian rules football clubs in Sydney
title: Sydney Football Club (NSWAFL)
